1
00:01:55,500 --> 00:02:00,458
[CROWD mutters]

2
00:02:02,750 --> 00:02:07,291
♪

3
00:02:07,375 --> 00:02:10,291
[LILY hums]

4
00:02:10,375 --> 00:02:12,000
Wait. You know this song?

5
00:02:12,083 --> 00:02:14,208
[LILY gasps]

6
00:02:14,291 --> 00:02:17,833
You said that Eve was
being protected by a witch.

7
00:02:17,916 --> 00:02:19,458
Have you ever met her, or...?

8
00:02:19,541 --> 00:02:22,791
[LILY] Mm-hm And she
wasn't the first, either.

9
00:02:22,875 --> 00:02:26,333
The protector must meet certain
criteria. There are rules.

10
00:02:26,416 --> 00:02:28,208
Like what?

11
00:02:28,291 --> 00:02:30,541
Being virginal is the
most important.

12
00:02:32,375 --> 00:02:35,125
So, why the lily?

13
00:02:35,208 --> 00:02:38,083
[LILY] Because white lilies
represent virtue.

14
00:02:40,750 --> 00:02:44,208
They're also known as
Madonna lilies. Lovely.

15
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,541
Lilies? If you say so.

16
00:02:49,625 --> 00:02:52,583
I wonder what kind of witch
this next one's gonna be?

17
00:02:57,291 --> 00:02:59,750
[gasps]

18
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:01,958
Are you surprised?

19
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:03,833
I'm surprised.

20
00:03:03,916 --> 00:03:06,125
Good to see you, Professor.

21
00:03:06,208 --> 00:03:08,583
[KANZAKI]
You got everyone together?

22
00:03:08,666 --> 00:03:11,833
When they awoke, they started
looking for others like them,

23
00:03:11,916 --> 00:03:13,791
and put together a contact list.

24
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:16,125
They developed the ability
to sense the former witch

25
00:03:16,208 --> 00:03:18,250
in one another.

26
00:03:18,333 --> 00:03:21,041
[YUKO] We all share
the same wish, though.

27
00:03:21,125 --> 00:03:23,916
We'd all like to
get to meet Haruto.

28
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,541
[MISAKI]
We hadn't made much progress,

29
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:27,791
each of us searching
for Haruto separately.

30
00:03:27,875 --> 00:03:30,000
So we've pooled our efforts to
track him down here in the

31
00:03:30,083 --> 00:03:31,416
real world.

32
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:32,833
You, too?

33
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:34,750
The scope of the Valanga royal
intelligence network is

34
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:36,666
at your service!

35
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,791
Have you discovered anything
of note that might lead us

36
00:03:38,875 --> 00:03:41,041
to Haruto here
in the real world?

37
00:03:41,125 --> 00:03:42,500
[KANZAKI]
No.

38
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:45,166
While we were witches, we
were able to sense something

39
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:48,708
in Haruto that made him quite
different from the others.

40
00:03:48,791 --> 00:03:49,916
"Different" how?

41
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,916
[MISAKI]
It has to do with time.

42
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,333
It's hard to explain,

43
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:57,375
but the time that envelops
Haruto is different.

44
00:03:57,458 --> 00:04:00,166
Unlike yours. Or anyone's.

45
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:01,666
[KANZAKI]
Hm?

46
00:04:01,750 --> 00:04:03,625
Don't look at me.
I don't get it.

47
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:05,958
Right now, the rest of the
witches are out searching

48
00:04:06,041 --> 00:04:09,250
the town for clues. Based on
what we felt in the dream world.

49
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:10,666
[KANZAKI] So you're all
using your feelings

50
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:13,208
as sort of a compass
to help track him down?

51
00:04:13,291 --> 00:04:14,458
[YUKO]
Yes.

52
00:04:14,541 --> 00:04:16,833
[KANZAKI] Seems like an
imprecise methodology.

53
00:04:16,916 --> 00:04:18,833
[MISAKI gasps] People who've
been in the dream world

54
00:04:18,916 --> 00:04:20,666
have a different
aura about them.

55
00:04:20,750 --> 00:04:23,208
Like how they say celebrities
project an aura.

56
00:04:23,291 --> 00:04:25,833
Sometimes you can just
tell by looking at them.

57
00:04:25,916 --> 00:04:27,458
So, what does it look like?

58
00:04:27,541 --> 00:04:30,833
It's simple, there's a
bit of a glow around them.

59
00:04:30,916 --> 00:04:32,500
First I've heard.

60
00:04:32,583 --> 00:04:35,625
Perhaps it's a side effect of
Sleeping Beauty Syndrome?

61
00:04:38,625 --> 00:04:40,500
Looks like another red door.

62
00:04:41,625 --> 00:04:44,041
[LILY] On the other side.
A witch's world.

63
00:04:46,041 --> 00:04:47,041
What's that sign?

64
00:04:47,125 --> 00:04:48,208
I don't know.

65
00:04:48,291 --> 00:04:50,375
Think it has something
to do with Eve?

66
00:04:50,458 --> 00:04:54,125
Maybe it's connected,
but I have no idea.

67
00:04:54,208 --> 00:04:56,625
This sounds like
a job... for him.

68
00:04:56,708 --> 00:05:00,000
Really? But, you guys
were fighting.

69
00:05:00,083 --> 00:05:02,666
So we can never speak
to each other again?

70
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:05,541
We disagreed, I'm not
going to be petty.

71
00:05:05,625 --> 00:05:06,458
[phone rings]

72
00:05:06,541 --> 00:05:08,416
[KANZAKI gasps]

73
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,625
Haruto!

74
00:05:09,708 --> 00:05:10,750
[WITCHES gasp]

75
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:12,500
Got it. I'm on my way.

76
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:14,041
[YUKO] Has something
happened to Haruto?

77
00:05:14,125 --> 00:05:15,625
[KANZAKI]
I have to go.

78
00:05:15,708 --> 00:05:17,041
[YUKO]
Huh?

79
00:05:17,125 --> 00:05:19,041
You can communicate with
the dream world through that.

80
00:05:19,125 --> 00:05:20,541
If you discover anything
new about Haruto,

81
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:23,208
let me know.
I'm counting on you.

82
00:05:26,708 --> 00:05:30,458
[EHYEH] Great Goddess Eve.
I feel your presence!

83
00:05:30,541 --> 00:05:34,041
My soul is set ablaze with
the magnanimity of your power!

84
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,708
Soon, you will wake!

85
00:05:35,791 --> 00:05:37,625
May your awakening be swift!

86
00:05:37,708 --> 00:05:40,708
For the sake of all
your lost children!

87
00:05:40,791 --> 00:05:44,708
How is the search going
for the girls out in the field?

88
00:05:44,791 --> 00:05:47,583
There have been no major
developments, as it stands.

89
00:05:47,666 --> 00:05:49,583
Then again, the only leads
we have to work from

90
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:51,583
are our feelings.

91
00:05:51,666 --> 00:05:53,125
[MARI] Haruto sounds
like a helluva guy.

92
00:05:53,208 --> 00:05:55,083
I'd like to meet him someday.

93
00:05:55,166 --> 00:05:57,291
That same wish is the hope
that drives us forward

94
00:05:57,375 --> 00:05:58,666
in our search.

95
00:05:58,750 --> 00:06:02,791
To speak face to face.
Not just a dream, but real.

96
00:06:02,875 --> 00:06:05,500
To truly meet Haruto!

97
00:06:05,583 --> 00:06:07,208
[KANZAKI]
Sorry to keep you waiting.

98
00:06:08,458 --> 00:06:11,750
I'm sorry. I was a jerk earlier.

99
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,958
--[KANZAKI chuckles]
--♪

100
00:06:14,041 --> 00:06:15,208
What is it?

101
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:18,833
That melody? Yes, that voice.

102
00:06:18,916 --> 00:06:20,583
You mean you've
heard it before?

103
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:21,583
My sister.

104
00:06:21,666 --> 00:06:23,083
--Huh?
--Really?

105
00:06:23,166 --> 00:06:26,541
Yes. Is she calling from
the other side of this door?

106
00:06:26,625 --> 00:06:28,458
It sounds like your
sister's voice?

107
00:06:28,541 --> 00:06:30,291
Well, what do you think, Lily?

108
00:06:30,375 --> 00:06:31,875
Wait, Lily's here?

109
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,208
[KANZAKI]
Hm.

110
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:40,458
She's right there!

111
00:06:40,541 --> 00:06:43,833
I've been standing
here the whole time.

112
00:06:43,916 --> 00:06:46,916
[KANZAKI] That's the crest of
the Thorn Cross Association.

113
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,041
They worship Eve as a goddess.

114
00:06:49,125 --> 00:06:50,166
Eve again?

115
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:52,166
You already know about Eve?

116
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:54,208
I know her better than anyone.

117
00:06:54,291 --> 00:06:56,166
The Professor mentioned
an emblem, earlier.

118
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,666
This is what he
was referring to.

119
00:06:58,750 --> 00:06:59,916
What is it?

120
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:02,500
I've seen it.
Those Thorn Crossers.

121
00:07:02,583 --> 00:07:05,416
They're preaching all over the
world about Eve awakening.

122
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,666
I'm worried about his sister.

123
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:09,791
Would one of you
girls accompany me?

124
00:07:09,875 --> 00:07:12,458
You want to go to the
Professor's laboratory?

125
00:07:12,541 --> 00:07:14,041
Yes.

126
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:16,458
If his sister experiences any
changes while he isn't around,

127
00:07:16,541 --> 00:07:19,958
we'll be on hand to
keep him up to date.

128
00:07:20,041 --> 00:07:21,583
Sure, I'll come.

129
00:07:23,541 --> 00:07:26,583
You girls keep an eye
on the place for me!

130
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:28,333
[KANZAKI] If what Lily
has told us is true.

131
00:07:28,416 --> 00:07:29,791
[LILY]
It is the truth!

132
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:33,083
What the Thorn Cross Association
says is the opposite.

133
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:34,500
[HARUTO] We'll find
out once we meet Eve.

134
00:07:34,583 --> 00:07:36,375
Meet her? And then what?

135
00:07:36,458 --> 00:07:38,666
She isn't like
the other witches.

136
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:41,750
Everyone dies if she
wakes up, right?

137
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:42,958
We kill her.

138
00:07:43,041 --> 00:07:44,041
[KANZAKI gasps]

139
00:07:44,125 --> 00:07:45,666
I was afraid it would
come to that.

140
00:07:45,750 --> 00:07:47,458
But how?

141
00:07:47,541 --> 00:07:51,166
Only Brother has the
power to destroy Eve.

142
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:53,875
And if he fails,
then we all die.

143
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:57,375
\Will you?

144
00:07:57,458 --> 00:07:59,500
[HARUTO sighs]

145
00:07:59,583 --> 00:08:01,458
I'd like to meet her first.

146
00:08:25,333 --> 00:08:27,750
[HARUTO grunts] What's with
the intimidation tactics?

147
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:30,500
We won't get very far unarmed.
We need some weapons!

148
00:08:30,583 --> 00:08:32,250
And where do you
suggest we find them?

149
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:34,000
We'll come up with something.
It's a dream!

150
00:08:34,083 --> 00:08:36,375
We aren't coming
up with anything!

151
00:08:39,416 --> 00:08:43,166
[gasps] It's a sign of things
stirring in the dream world

152
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:45,375
where the goddess slumbers!

153
00:08:50,291 --> 00:08:53,958
[YURINA] Yield, intruders.
On your knees.

154
00:08:54,041 --> 00:08:57,750
I will permit you to
gaze upon my visage.

155
00:08:57,833 --> 00:09:00,125
[HARUTO] She must be
the witch of this world.

156
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:02,000
I can't detect the
witch's thoughts.

157
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:03,416
There's only the cannons.

158
00:09:03,500 --> 00:09:06,500
But they were created
by a different entity.

159
00:09:06,583 --> 00:09:10,500
That isn't the issue.
That's my sister.

160
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:14,708
[YURINA] I am the Witch of
White Lilies. I protect Eve.

161
00:09:14,791 --> 00:09:17,500
My virtue guards her
door from invaders.

162
00:09:17,583 --> 00:09:20,125
What're you talking about?

163
00:09:20,208 --> 00:09:23,458
Yurina! It's me, your brother!
I'm here for you!

164
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:34,000
[ALL shout]

165
00:09:36,416 --> 00:09:38,166
[YURINA chuckles]

166
00:09:41,500 --> 00:09:43,250
Something tells me the
witch didn't recognize you

167
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:44,666
as her brother.

168
00:09:47,291 --> 00:09:50,583
I see. Eve is trying
to get rid of me.

169
00:09:50,666 --> 00:09:51,791
Do what?

170
00:09:51,875 --> 00:09:54,250
[LILY] This witch is
being controlled by Eve.

171
00:09:54,333 --> 00:09:56,833
That's why I couldn't
delve into her thoughts.

172
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:59,791
We didn't step into a dream
world controlled by the witch.

173
00:09:59,875 --> 00:10:01,291
This is Eve's world!

174
00:10:01,375 --> 00:10:03,875
[AIRI pants, grunts]

175
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:05,958
What didja stop for?

176
00:10:08,625 --> 00:10:09,958
A hospital?

177
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:13,666
Since the incident, I've come
here a number of times.

178
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:17,375
[AIRI gasps] Why now?
What do you need?

179
00:10:17,458 --> 00:10:21,125
It's been a while. I'm paying
my respects to the doctor.

180
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:24,875
Huh? Come on! We're getting
sidetracked here!

181
00:10:27,291 --> 00:10:28,625
[MANA]
Doctor.

182
00:10:28,708 --> 00:10:32,625
Ah! It's you. And this
is your friend?

183
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:35,375
I'm Airi Kojima.
It's nice to meet you.

184
00:10:35,458 --> 00:10:36,750
Huh?

185
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:40,000
Girl, your doctor looks
like a hot pop star!

186
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:42,958
I'm happy for you. Good to
see you with a friend.

187
00:10:43,041 --> 00:10:44,291
You are friends, right?

188
00:10:44,375 --> 00:10:47,625
Yeah, you know it!
We're thick as thieves, doc!

189
00:10:47,708 --> 00:10:50,458
We were just in the area,
so Mana here decided we should

190
00:10:50,541 --> 00:10:52,250
drop in and say hello!

191
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:53,500
[MANA gasps]

192
00:10:54,708 --> 00:10:56,500
[AIRI gasps]
Was that?

193
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,375
[MANA]
Mm-hm.

194
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:02,750
Ah yes, that patient. He's been
comatose for a long time.

195
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,375
The poor young man
hasn't been awake

196
00:11:04,458 --> 00:11:06,916
since before he
was brought to us.

197
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,083
Did you feel it?

198
00:11:08,166 --> 00:11:11,458
Yeah. Just what it
felt like in my dream.

199
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:12,666
[AKITO]
Hm?

200
00:11:16,958 --> 00:11:18,250
[LILY shouts]

201
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:22,041
[HARUTO]
Hang in there, Lily!

202
00:11:22,125 --> 00:11:25,166
I'm okay. Just give me a second.

203
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,833
I'm getting sick of this witch!

204
00:11:26,916 --> 00:11:29,791
It isn't right to shoot
at children like this!

205
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:32,750
All the same,
she's still my sister.

206
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:40,666
That's his name.

207
00:11:40,750 --> 00:11:41,916
Yeah.

208
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,291
We've found him.

209
00:11:43,375 --> 00:11:45,208
Hold on.

210
00:11:45,291 --> 00:11:47,708
There's a chance it could be
someone with the same name.

211
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:51,083
But we felt it! That hint
of the dream world.

212
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:52,458
We'll make sure.

213
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:53,958
But how?

214
00:12:07,166 --> 00:12:11,625
[KANZAKI] Yurina! I thought
I understood what you wanted.

215
00:12:11,708 --> 00:12:13,000
But was I wrong?

216
00:12:13,083 --> 00:12:15,208
Was becoming an idol
something you never intended?

217
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:17,000
[HARUTO]
Hm? An idol?

218
00:12:17,083 --> 00:12:18,500
Indeed.

219
00:12:18,583 --> 00:12:20,833
Yurina passed an audition
that her friend had signed her

220
00:12:20,916 --> 00:12:23,833
up for, and quickly
became an idol sensation.

221
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:26,125
She had so many people
cheering for her.

222
00:12:26,208 --> 00:12:29,958
She wore herself out trying
to meet all their expectations.

223
00:12:30,041 --> 00:12:32,250
And I know you weren't trying
to run from your problems

224
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:34,916
by developing Sleeping
Beauty Syndrome.

225
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,000
You kept working hard
out of a sense of duty,

226
00:12:37,083 --> 00:12:40,333
but the same sense of duty that
drove you brought you to a stop.

227
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:45,291
Wake up, Yurina!
Enough, already!

228
00:12:45,375 --> 00:12:47,583
Sleeping Beauty
Syndrome is like death.

229
00:12:47,666 --> 00:12:49,166
But you are still alive!

230
00:12:49,250 --> 00:12:52,875
And as long as you are, you can
still choose a different path!

231
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:57,916
[HARUTO]
Professor!

232
00:13:00,375 --> 00:13:02,041
That's a good question.

233
00:13:02,125 --> 00:13:04,166
We just have to
ask them flat out.

234
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:05,208
I suppose so.

235
00:13:05,291 --> 00:13:06,541
--[phone beeps]
--[YUKO gasps]

236
00:13:06,625 --> 00:13:08,291
What's wrong?

237
00:13:10,083 --> 00:13:11,375
Kayo who?

238
00:13:11,458 --> 00:13:13,500
Kayo? The Witch of First Love.

239
00:13:13,583 --> 00:13:15,375
Witch of First Love?

240
00:13:15,458 --> 00:13:18,250
But she passed away,
didn't she?

241
00:13:18,333 --> 00:13:21,875
She can't come to us,
but perhaps she left part

242
00:13:21,958 --> 00:13:24,125
of her soul in this world
to look after Haruto?

243
00:13:24,208 --> 00:13:27,625
Awesome! You just got
a text from a ghost!

244
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:29,666
I'll try to text her back.

245
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:33,458
[MISAKI]
That's so cool!

246
00:13:33,541 --> 00:13:35,958
[AIRI]
You're kidding. A dead person?

247
00:13:37,125 --> 00:13:38,041
Oh. Hi.

248
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:40,166
[AIRI gasps]

249
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:41,916
[MANA]
We can see her.

250
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:43,875
We sure can.

251
00:13:43,958 --> 00:13:45,208
[KAYO chuckles]

252
00:13:51,958 --> 00:13:54,000
Enough! Stop this!

253
00:13:55,750 --> 00:13:56,958
[phone rings]

254
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:59,041
[KANZAKI grunts]

255
00:13:59,125 --> 00:14:00,916
What's up? I'm a little
busy right now.

256
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:03,833
We've finally tracked down
Haruto in the real world.

257
00:14:09,541 --> 00:14:11,291
Huh? What was that?

258
00:14:11,375 --> 00:14:14,708
I said, we know where
Haruto is now!

259
00:14:14,791 --> 00:14:17,083
[YUKO gasps]

260
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:20,750
What's that noise? It's so loud!

261
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:21,916
[YUKO]
Huh?

262
00:14:22,375 --> 00:14:26,166
♪

263
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:30,000
I'm sorry, Yuko, but I
can't chat at the moment.

264
00:14:35,125 --> 00:14:37,041
This world has
started to collapse.

265
00:14:37,125 --> 00:14:38,291
It what?

266
00:14:38,375 --> 00:14:41,791
We'll all die. The witch too.

267
00:14:41,875 --> 00:14:44,041
That voice, it's hers!

268
00:14:44,125 --> 00:14:45,416
You know who it is?

269
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:48,625
It's Yurina! The idol
idols want to be!

270
00:14:48,708 --> 00:14:50,000
Can you save her?

271
00:14:50,083 --> 00:14:51,375
I can try!

272
00:14:51,458 --> 00:14:54,375
[NENE] You're a witch.
All you have to do is dream.

273
00:14:54,458 --> 00:14:56,125
Now hurry up and go to sleep!

274
00:14:56,208 --> 00:15:01,166
♪

275
00:15:05,208 --> 00:15:06,541
Who are you?

276
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,041
Misaki?

277
00:15:14,125 --> 00:15:18,541
[MISAKI] Haruto. It's an eye for
an eye, and an idol for an idol.

278
00:15:18,625 --> 00:15:20,000
I don't really follow,
but at this point,

279
00:15:20,083 --> 00:15:22,291
I feel we've exhausted
our other options.

280
00:15:22,375 --> 00:15:26,125
[MISAKI sighs]
Yurina. You're an inspiration!

281
00:15:26,208 --> 00:15:27,458
Out of my way!

282
00:15:33,541 --> 00:15:35,583
There's only so much
Misaki is going to be able to do

283
00:15:35,666 --> 00:15:36,958
by herself!

284
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:39,041
Eve seeks purity above all else.

285
00:15:39,125 --> 00:15:40,958
Which means, if we
taint that purity,

286
00:15:41,041 --> 00:15:44,166
eve will withdraw, and have no
further need for this witch.

287
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:45,958
Easier said than done.

288
00:15:46,041 --> 00:15:47,375
Be gone, you pest!

289
00:15:47,458 --> 00:15:49,250
[MISAKI]
Yurina, you have to wake up!

290
00:15:49,333 --> 00:15:51,333
I will not be distracted
from my mission!

291
00:15:51,416 --> 00:15:53,541
The goddess is sleeping.
Be gone!

292
00:15:53,625 --> 00:15:57,916
[MISAKI grunts]

293
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,541
You told me that I'll have
to kill Eve, didn't you?

294
00:16:00,625 --> 00:16:02,500
That's right.

295
00:16:02,583 --> 00:16:03,666
[HARUTO]
I thought of how to do it.

296
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:04,875
[LILY gasps]

297
00:16:06,291 --> 00:16:08,750
I was thinking I might take
an approach like this.

298
00:16:08,833 --> 00:16:10,000
[LILY gasps]

299
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:22,166
[YURINA]
Lily? Get lost!

300
00:16:24,166 --> 00:16:25,833
[BOTH grunt]

301
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:30,291
You did it! Great job!

302
00:16:30,375 --> 00:16:32,875
[HARUTO] Eve is watching
me through you, right?

303
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:33,958
Then look at me.

304
00:16:34,041 --> 00:16:36,166
--Let me go! Right now!
--Not happening.

305
00:16:39,041 --> 00:16:41,291
[KANZAKI]
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

306
00:16:43,416 --> 00:16:47,541
[screams]

307
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:50,208
I've spoiled the purity
of your white lily.

308
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:53,625
[YURINA gasps]

309
00:16:53,708 --> 00:16:55,000
[HARUTO]
Hi there.

310
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:57,625
Haruto! What were you thinking?

311
00:16:57,708 --> 00:16:59,791
Oh, no! What'd you do?

312
00:16:59,875 --> 00:17:00,750
I liked it.

313
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:03,541
Eve is no longer with her.

314
00:17:03,625 --> 00:17:05,250
Worse ways to lose, right?

315
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:07,041
[KANZAKI]
Don't go spiking the ball!

316
00:17:07,125 --> 00:17:09,416
How dare you try to play
my sister like that!

317
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:10,916
And right in front of me?

318
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,833
You're going to answer for what
you did to her back there!

319
00:17:12,916 --> 00:17:15,791
Ow! Ow! Whaddaya mean, answer?

320
00:17:17,625 --> 00:17:19,458
Come on, Brother,
that's enough!

321
00:17:19,541 --> 00:17:20,500
You mean?

322
00:17:20,583 --> 00:17:22,875
What? Even as a cat,
she could tell?

323
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:26,333
Yurina! You're back
to your old self!

324
00:17:26,416 --> 00:17:27,583
Well, that should do it!

325
00:17:27,666 --> 00:17:28,708
Should do what?

326
00:17:28,791 --> 00:17:30,208
Speaking as an idol,

327
00:17:30,291 --> 00:17:33,000
this little photo could cause
a life-shattering scandal.

328
00:17:33,083 --> 00:17:35,375
No way! How'd you even get
that in the first place?

329
00:17:35,458 --> 00:17:38,125
This is a dream.
Anything can happen.

330
00:17:38,208 --> 00:17:40,666
Don't even think about trying
to sell those to the tabloids!

331
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:42,666
[MISAKI chuckles]

332
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:44,791
[KANZAKI shouts]

333
00:17:44,875 --> 00:17:48,041
The Professor's definitely an
older brother, that's for sure.

334
00:17:48,125 --> 00:17:50,541
Yurina. Let's sing together!

335
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:51,291
[YURINA]
Huh?

336
00:17:51,375 --> 00:17:52,958
We have to destroy that.

337
00:17:53,041 --> 00:17:55,583
[YURINA] Whoa. Wait a second.
What's going on?

338
00:17:55,666 --> 00:17:57,666
[MISAKI] An evil goddess is
lurking on the other side

339
00:17:57,750 --> 00:17:58,875
of that fort.

340
00:17:58,958 --> 00:18:00,916
That's right. So sing!

341
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,791
And you are who?

342
00:18:03,875 --> 00:18:05,416
A fan of yours.

343
00:18:05,500 --> 00:18:06,625
Fan?

344
00:18:16,166 --> 00:18:16,708
Now what?

345
00:18:16,791 --> 00:18:21,750
[roaring]

346
00:18:25,625 --> 00:18:27,291
[KANZAKI]
Yurina. A song?

347
00:18:27,375 --> 00:18:28,875
[LILY]
Or else we'll die.

348
00:18:28,958 --> 00:18:31,625
So if I start to sing,
everyone will be saved?

349
00:18:31,708 --> 00:18:34,000
That's right. Including you.

350
00:18:47,791 --> 00:18:52,750
♪

351
00:18:57,791 --> 00:19:00,791
You've grown
stronger too, Misaki.

352
00:19:08,625 --> 00:19:09,833
[MISAKI grunts]

353
00:19:16,166 --> 00:19:17,500
Awesome.

354
00:19:29,791 --> 00:19:34,750
♪

355
00:19:39,208 --> 00:19:40,750
Seems like you enjoyed yourself.

356
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:42,625
Well, this is a dream.

357
00:19:55,125 --> 00:19:56,750
Is that the final door?

358
00:19:56,833 --> 00:19:58,958
Wait. It's the same door
that you use, isn't it?

359
00:19:59,041 --> 00:20:00,958
[LILY gasps]

360
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:04,958
Now, would you take
Yurina out of here?

361
00:20:05,041 --> 00:20:06,458
Sure.

362
00:20:06,541 --> 00:20:08,375
And make sure not to let Eve
get into your head again.

363
00:20:08,458 --> 00:20:10,041
Catch you later! Be safe!

364
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:13,208
"Catch you later"?
Haruto just kissed you!

365
00:20:13,291 --> 00:20:14,500
Or does that not concern you?

366
00:20:14,583 --> 00:20:15,958
Hey, take it easy, will ya?

367
00:20:16,041 --> 00:20:18,000
You're giving off
an old-fogey vibe.

368
00:20:18,083 --> 00:20:20,333
Fogey? That's not fair!

369
00:20:31,958 --> 00:20:33,958
[YURINA grunts]

370
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:38,958
Welcome back to the world.

371
00:20:39,041 --> 00:20:40,583
[YURINA]
Who are you?

372
00:20:40,666 --> 00:20:43,291
Someone else who was saved by
the young man you just met.

373
00:20:43,375 --> 00:20:45,291
He's the reason you're awake.

374
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:51,416
Get ready. I'm going to send an
image of Haruto to everyone.

375
00:20:57,750 --> 00:21:02,708
[EKG beeps]

376
00:21:04,708 --> 00:21:07,583
That's him?
Is that really Haruto?

377
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:10,000
[NENE] All those tubes.
What happened to him?

378
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:14,000
[CROWD chatters]

379
00:21:14,083 --> 00:21:15,250
You saw?

380
00:21:15,333 --> 00:21:16,583
Yes.

381
00:21:16,666 --> 00:21:18,083
What does it mean?

382
00:21:18,166 --> 00:21:20,041
How long has he been asleep?

383
00:21:23,583 --> 00:21:25,083
So on the other
side of that door,

384
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:27,000
the goddess Eve is sleeping.

385
00:21:27,083 --> 00:21:28,500
No. She's awake now.

386
00:21:28,583 --> 00:21:29,791
What?

387
00:21:29,875 --> 00:21:31,875
Eve's awake? Damn.

388
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:33,041
[LILY]
Mm.

389
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:42,291
[EHYEH gasps]
The miracle! The glory!

390
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:45,583
The goddess whom we worship,
has finally awakened!

391
00:21:45,666 --> 00:21:48,166
The time of our
salvation is at hand!

392
00:21:48,250 --> 00:21:53,208
[CROWD mutters, gasps]

393
00:21:55,541 --> 00:21:57,666
It's the beginning of the end.

394
00:22:02,166 --> 00:22:04,791
I suppose it's time
to meet this goddess.

395
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:18,125
♪

396
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:49,125
[LILY]
The dream comes to an end.

397
00:23:49,208 --> 00:23:51,083
[EGOS]
It ends, baa.

398
00:23:51,166 --> 00:23:54,291
[LILY] Next time's dream is:
"Eve's Sigh."

